Executive Profile
Charles E. Schwabe  EVP and Secretary, Howard Bancorp, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 0 Board Members in 0 different organizations across 2 different industries.62--
Background

		Mr. Charles E. Schwabe, also known as Charlie, has been an Executive Vice President, Secretary, Chief Strategic Risk Officer of Howard BankExecutive Vice President of Howard Bank, Secretary of Howard BanCorp Inc. and Howard Bank since December 2005 and December 2012. Mr. Schwabe served as Chief Administrative Officer, Chief Risk Officer  Howard Bank since December 2005 until December 2014. Mr. Schwabe has been Chief Risk Officer of Howard Bank, Inc. since December 2014 ... and has been its Executive Vice President and Secretary since 2004. Mr. Schwabe served as Chief Administrative Officer and Chief Information Officer of Howard Bank Inc. since 2004 until December 2014. Mr. Schwabe served as an Chief Administrative Officer and Chief Information Officer of Howard BanCorp Inc. since December 2005 until December 2014. Mr. Schwabe served as Chief Administrative Officer, Chief Information Officer of Howard Bank since 2004 until December 2014. He served as Information Security Officer and Compliance Officer at Howard Bank. He served as Chief Operational Risk Officer of Howard Bancorp Inc., and its subsidiary Howard Bank. He has 15 years of banking management experience and another 7 years as a marketing strategy consultant to the banking, retail and business services industries. He served as Chief Operational Risk Officer of Howard BanCorp. Inc and also as Secretary since December 2005. He provides leadership for the operations, information technology, human resources, loan documentation, deposit management and other areas of administration including Howard's strategic partnership outsourcing arrangements. Prior to joining the organizing group for Howard Bank, Mr. Schwabe was employed by Allfirst Bank from 1988 to April 2003. He served as Senior Vice President and Manager for the Customer Relationship Management Program as well as the Strategy and Planning Director for the Technology, eCommerce and Operations Division of Allfirst Bank. At Allfirst Bank, Mr. Schwabe was also Vice President of Strategic Planning for the Mergers and Acquisitions Division and Vice President and Group Marketing Head for small business and retail product development and management. Prior to working at Allfirst Bank, he was a Consultant and Senior Manager for a marketing firm that specialized in the health care and financial services industries. Mr. Schwabe serves as a Member of the Advisory Board of Howard Bank. He serves as the President of the Baltimore chapter of the American Marketing Association and has been an Instructor in Marketing, Research and Economics at Goucher College and Drexel University. He serves on Loyola College's Marketing Advisory Board and as a Member of the Cockeysville Middle School Improvement Team. He serves as Treasurer of the Atlantic Lacrosse Club and is a Member of the Columbia Festival of the Arts Marketing Advisory Board. Mr. Schwabe has also been a Coach for the Carroll Manor lacrosse, field hockey, softball and basketball programs.Read Full Background




